Dialogue: 1,0:04:21.63,0:04:23.55,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}where both sides of it have been ruled out
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.63,0:04:23.55,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}它的两边都已经被排除了
Dialogue: 1,0:04:23.55,0:04:27.13,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and we can finally place our first light bulb in the puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.55,0:04:27.13,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而我们终于可以把第一个灯泡放进去了
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.13,0:04:32.57,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and after that placing that light bulb in the puzzle we can place the light bulb next to this one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.13,0:04:32.57,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}放了这个灯泡之后，我们就可以放这个1旁边的灯泡
Dialogue: 1,0:04:32.57,0:04:35.58,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}we could place the two light bulbs next to this two
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.57,0:04:35.58,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们能放这两个灯泡在这个2旁边
Dialogue: 1,0:04:35.58,0:04:38.72,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}which then allow us to place the two light bulbs next to this two
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.58,0:04:38.72,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后这就让我们可以在这个2旁边放这两个灯泡
Dialogue: 1,0:04:38.72,0:04:41.40,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}which allow us to place the light bulb next to this one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.72,0:04:41.40,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后又可以在这个1旁边放这个灯泡
Dialogue: 1,0:04:41.40,0:04:42.68,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and then these two
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.40,0:04:42.68,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后这两个
Dialogue: 1,0:04:42.68,0:04:43.71,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and then this one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.68,0:04:43.71,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后这一个
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.71,0:04:44.60,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and then these two
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.71,0:04:44.60,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后是这两个
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.60,0:04:45.69,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and these two
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.60,0:04:45.69,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}和这两个
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.69,0:04:46.52,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and this one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.69,0:04:46.52,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}和这一个
Dialogue: 1,0:04:46.52,0:04:47.42,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and these two
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.52,0:04:47.42,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}和这两个
Dialogue: 1,0:04:47.42,0:04:52.92,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and it just keeps going until we place the last two next to these
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.42,0:04:52.92,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}一直到我们把最后这个两个放进去
Dialogue: 1,0:04:52.92,0:04:57.02,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and to finish the puzzle there is one square remaining that hasn't been illuminated
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.92,0:04:57.02,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}要完成这个谜题，还剩一个格子没被照亮
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.02,0:04:59.77,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and of course we have to put the final light bulb there
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.02,0:04:59.77,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}当然了，我们得把最后一个灯泡放在这里
Dialogue: 1,0:04:59.77,0:05:02.84,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and that is the solution to this Akari puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.77,0:05:02.84,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而这就是这个点灯游戏的解法
Dialogue: 1,0:05:02.84,0:05:07.96,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and there are so many things about this puzzle that are remarkable
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.84,0:05:07.96,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这个谜题里有很多了不起的地方
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.96,0:05:11.42,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um you know there's this whole sense of playfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.96,0:05:11.42,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你知道，整个过程有一种很有乐趣的感觉
Dialogue: 1,0:05:11.42,0:05:16.03,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}as you're going through the puzzle and taking these steps one leading to the next leading to the next
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.42,0:05:16.03,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你在解决这个谜题的过程中，做了这样一些步骤，一个接一个的，前一个解释了下一个
Dialogue: 1,0:05:16.03,0:05:26.97,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}there's this repeated pattern or motif where you're using the same lemma or the same uh pattern or technique over and over again to create this chain repetition of logic
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.03,0:05:26.97,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}有这样一个重复的模式，你一遍又一遍用同样的规律或技巧来创造这样一个逻辑链
Dialogue: 1,0:05:26.97,0:05:34.97,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um and then there's a variant or a twist on that lemma where you know you're using it once and then a second time on the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.97,0:05:34.97,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后这样的规律又有一个变体或转变，你在同一事物上使用了一次然后又用第二次
Dialogue: 1,0:05:34.97,0:05:44.06,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um and there's the whole setup and payoff like you do one lap around the grid to rule out one set of spaces and then you do a second lap which rules out a second set of spaces
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.97,0:05:44.06,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}还有这整个的布置，就像你绕着格子过一趟，排除了些地方，然后又过一遍，又排除了一组格子
Dialogue: 1,0:05:44.06,0:05:47.39,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and then results in the final placement of the light bulbs
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.06,0:05:47.39,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后得到了灯泡的最终位置
Dialogue: 1,0:05:47.39,0:05:53.08,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}the whole surprise ending where there's only one space left is sort of um a cherry on top
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.39,0:05:53.08,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而最后只剩下一个空格这样一个惊喜的结局，又有点锦上添花的感觉
Dialogue: 1,0:05:53.08,0:05:57.50,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}but you know you look at a puzzle like this and there can be no doubt that it was created by a human
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.08,0:05:57.50,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但你看到这样的谜题时，毫无疑问它是由人类创作的
Dialogue: 1,0:05:57.50,0:06:01.60,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}this puzzle is just like it's beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.50,0:06:01.60,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这个谜题的设计就很美丽
Dialogue: 2,0:06:01.60,0:06:16.25,Annote,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}（译者注：《超级马里奥：3D》的设计师 林田宏一 所提出的四步关卡设计法，即「起承転結」（起承转合），引入、发展、转折和总结）
Dialogue: 1,0:06:01.60,0:06:07.55,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um there's some steps of how it's created that feel a little bit similar to sort of the Nintendo 4 step level design
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.60,0:06:07.55,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}它的制作步骤有点类似于任天堂的四步关卡设计法
Dialogue: 1,0:06:07.55,0:06:16.25,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}where you have something new and then you sort of introduce it and then create a twist on it and then um you know put it together to into a finale
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.55,0:06:16.25,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}也就是你有些新的东西，然后引入它，再创造一个转折点，再合到一起成为结局
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.25,0:06:20.09,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}uh and then you know you might throw away this idea for your next puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.25,0:06:20.09,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后再下个谜题中你可能会抛弃这个想法
Dialogue: 1,0:06:20.09,0:06:22.84,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um but there's something special going on here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.09,0:06:22.84,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但这里面也发生着一些很特别的事情
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.84,0:06:29.12,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and it makes the experience of solving this puzzle more than just one of um you know finding the answer or something
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.84,0:06:29.12,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而这使得解谜的体验不仅仅是去找到答案
Dialogue: 1,0:06:29.12,0:06:33.47,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}it's like communicating with the author of this puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.12,0:06:33.47,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}它就像是在和这个谜题的作者交流一样
Dialogue: 1,0:06:33.47,0:06:38.78,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and I’ll share with you a quote from Nobuhiko Kanamoto who was the editor of Nikoli
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.47,0:06:38.78,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我和你们分享Nikoli的编辑Nobuhiko Kanamoto的一段话
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.78,0:06:45.82,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and this is way back this is two decades ago before sudoku took over in the west
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.78,0:06:45.82,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这是二十年前的一段话了，那时候数独还没在西方流行开来
Dialogue: 1,0:06:45.82,0:06:50.75,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}this is when sudoku that was computer generated was just starting to come out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.82,0:06:50.75,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}正是计算机生成的数独刚刚开始出现的时候
Dialogue: 1,0:06:50.75,0:07:01.31,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and um Kanamoto-san remarks that computer-generated sudoku puzzles are sort of lacking that vital ingredient that makes puzzles enjoyable this sense of communication
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.75,0:07:01.31,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}Kanamoto先生指出：“计算机生成的数独谜题缺少一种使谜题玩起来很愉悦的重要因素， \N 即缺少解题者和创作者之间的交流感”
Dialogue: 1,0:07:01.31,0:07:12.64,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and you know what ended up happening was these sort of massive uh numbers of computer-generated sudoku puzzles flooded the newspapers in the west and the puzzle books in the west
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:12.64,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你知道，后来的结果是，大量计算机生成的数独谜题充斥着西方的报纸和谜题书籍
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.64,0:07:18.20,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and as a result um you know subscribers of Nikoli and other Japanese puzzle magazines
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.64,0:07:18.20,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而结果，你知道，Nikoli还有其他日本谜题杂志的订阅者们
Dialogue: 1,0:07:18.20,0:07:21.21,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}they had this sort of taste for handcrafted puzzles
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:21.21,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}他们对手工制作的谜题有了一定的品味
Dialogue: 1,0:07:21.21,0:07:26.52,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}uh but folks in the west never developed that taste they were just bombarded with computer-generated puzzles
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.21,0:07:26.52,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但西方人从来没有发展出这种品味，只会被电脑生成的谜题“轰炸”
Dialogue: 1,0:07:26.52,0:07:29.66,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}which uh is sort of a tragedy in some ways
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.52,0:07:29.66,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这在某种程度上是个悲剧
Dialogue: 1,0:07:29.66,0:07:38.62,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}because the subtlety and excitement of really good sudoku puzzles or other paper-based logic puzzles um has been lost
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.66,0:07:38.62,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}因为真正好的数独或其他纸质逻辑谜题的精巧性和刺激性已经丧失了
Dialogue: 1,0:07:38.62,0:07:45.66,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and a lot of people think of sudoku as sort of a tired boring not that interesting not that novel puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.62,0:07:45.66,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}很多人都认为数独是一种乏味的、无趣的、没有新意的谜题
Dialogue: 1,0:07:45.66,0:07:52.44,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um but there are good sudokus this is a book uh by Thomas Snyder called the art of sudoku
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.66,0:07:52.44,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但也有好的数独，这本书是Thomas Snyder写的，叫做《数独的艺术》(The Art of Sudoku)
Dialogue: 1,0:07:52.44,0:07:55.77,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and uh it's just one of many examples
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.44,0:07:55.77,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这只是其中一个例子
Dialogue: 1,0:07:55.77,0:08:00.12,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}but the puzzles in this book they're not only artfully designed and laid out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.77,0:08:00.12,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这本书中的谜题不仅有艺术性的设计和布局
Dialogue: 1,0:08:00.12,0:08:04.09,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}but they also have this sort of flow between the puzzle maker and solver
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.12,0:08:04.09,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}而且其中有种解谜者和设计者之间流畅的交流
Dialogue: 1,0:08:04.09,0:08:09.47,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}where you're taking on a journey from starting the puzzle to the end where more and more things are revealed to you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.09,0:08:09.47,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}你就像开启了一段旅程，从起点到终点，里面的东西逐渐揭示给你
Dialogue: 1,0:08:09.47,0:08:16.76,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and if you've never done a good sudoku puzzle I would highly recommend you actually try them um
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.47,0:08:16.76,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}如果你从来没有做过一个好的数独谜题，我强烈建议你去试试
Dialogue: 1,0:08:16.76,0:08:22.59,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}better yet go on “cracking the cryptic” YouTube channel and look at some of the more interesting sudokus that they've done
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:22.59,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}可以去“Cracking The Cryptic”这个油管频道看看，他们做了些非常有趣的数独谜题
Dialogue: 1,0:08:22.59,0:08:25.40,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and give them a try yourself um
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.59,0:08:25.40,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}然后再自己试试
Dialogue: 1,0:08:25.40,0:08:28.99,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}but you know the question is how do you design puzzles like that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.40,0:08:28.99,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但你知道，我们的问题是，我们如何才能设计这样的谜题？
Dialogue: 1,0:08:28.99,0:08:32.44,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and there is a trick there is a technique that allows us to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.99,0:08:32.44,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}有一个诀窍和技巧可以让我们做到这一点
Dialogue: 1,0:08:32.44,0:08:38.33,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and it's um well the technique is called “designing from the front” aka “forward design”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.44,0:08:38.33,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这个技巧叫做「从正面设计」，也即“前向设计”
Dialogue: 1,0:08:38.33,0:08:41.72,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and I will show you a demo of this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.33,0:08:41.72,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我给你们演示一下
Dialogue: 1,0:08:41.72,0:08:47.04,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um and we're going to open up the creator for these types of puzzles
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.72,0:08:47.04,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我把这个谜题的编辑器模式打开一下
Dialogue: 1,0:08:47.04,0:08:49.28,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um and I’m literally yoloing it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.04,0:08:49.28,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这里我就冒个险了
Dialogue: 1,0:08:49.28,0:08:53.82,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}like when I did the recording of the GDC talk I sort of had a plan of what I’m going to do
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.28,0:08:53.82,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}当我在录正式的GDC演讲的时候我提前规划好了要怎么做的
Dialogue: 1,0:08:53.82,0:08:56.89,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}but here I’m literally just going to make it up as I go
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:56.89,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}但这里，我就直接即兴创作了
Dialogue: 1,0:08:56.89,0:09:00.22,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}and so, we're creating an Akari puzzle
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.89,0:09:00.22,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}那么，我们是要创作一个点灯游戏
Dialogue: 1,0:09:00.22,0:09:04.44,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}let's make a low difficulty one and insert lots of easy steps
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.22,0:09:04.44,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}让我们做一个低难度的，插入些简单的步骤
Dialogue: 1,0:09:04.44,0:09:07.84,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}something we might do is let's put in a zero
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.44,0:09:07.84,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}我们能做的是，我们先放个0进去
Dialogue: 1,0:09:07.84,0:09:10.52,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}a zero is sort of an obvious place to get started
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.84,0:09:10.52,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}0是一个很明显的可以作为起点的地方
Dialogue: 1,0:09:10.52,0:09:15.32,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}it's a so-called “hook” it's a thing that the player will immediately take their pencil and put in something
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.52,0:09:15.32,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}这就是一个所谓的引子，是一个能让玩家立即拿起笔填上的东西
Dialogue: 1,0:09:15.32,0:09:17.88,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}um and let me just zoom out a tick
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.32,0:09:17.88,Chi,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}让我缩小一点
Dialogue: 1,0:09:17.88,0:09:23.64,Eng,,0,0,0,,{\fad(120,120)}the method that we're using here is we're gonna place clues and solve the puzzle at the same time
